adjective.description: Not princelike; not characteristic of or befitting a prince.

adverb.description: In an unprincely manner; in a manner not befitting a prince.

origin: Late 16th century; earliest use found in John Stubbs (c1541–1590), religious writer. From un- + princelike<br>late 16th century; earliest use found in Robert Wilmot (b. c1550), playwright and Church of England clergyman. From un- + princelike.
